title: The Best Of The Move
description:
Feel free to drop a comment!

The Move were one of the leading British rock bands of the 1960s from
Birmingham, England, and were among the most popular British bands not to find any success in the US. The Move were led by guitarist, singer and songwriter Roy Wood.
Beside Wood, the original members of The Move in 1966 were drummer Bev Bevan, bassist Chris "Ace" Kefford, vocalist Carl Wayne and guitarist Trevor Burton. The concluding members in 1972 were the trio of Wood, Bevan and guitarist-pianist Jeff Lynne, who is commonly credited, along with Wood, with
transitioning the group into The Electric Light Orchestra.

This album is released on Music Club MCCD 009.
